<h1 style="background-color:powderblue;">Ibn An Nafis</h1>
<h2 style="background-color:#EAF2F8;">ʿIbn Al-Nafis was an Arab polymath whose areas of work included  medicine, surgery, physiology, anatomy, biology, Islamic studies, jurisprudence, and philosophy. He had a major contribution to the studies of 
the circulatory system, also being the first to describe the pulmonary 
circulation of blood, embedding a deep impact to the medicinal studies that 
we use and depend on today.</h2>


